  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "After recording the resurrection appearances,",
      "the writer explains why these events were written."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "purpose",
        "icon": "menu_book",
        "label": { "en": "Many Other Signs" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus did many other miraculous signs",
          "in the presence of his disciples,",
          "which are not recorded in this book."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "belief",
        "icon": "lightbulb",
        "label": { "en": "Written So That You May Believe" },
        "lines": [
          "But these are written",
          "that you may believe",
          "that Jesus is the Christ,",
          "the Son of God,",
          "and that by believing",
          "you may have life",
          "in his name."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "If these events were written so that you may believe and have life, what do you think belief means in this context?"
  },
